FT  12 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Thos Locker picks up to Pounds 306,000
Thomas Locker (Holdings), the general engineering group, recovered in the
second half but still showed a substantial reduction in profits for the year
to March 31.
A recommended final dividend of 0.65p makes 1p, compared with 1.6p. Earnings
per share were 0.32p (2.75p).
After a loss of Pounds 217,000 at midterm, the year's profit worked through
at Pounds 306,000 on turnover of Pounds 36m, against Pounds 1.64m from sales
of Pounds 40.5m.
